values:
this summer break has been the best so far. i went to south carolina to visit my grandma for a week in june.&nbsp; i went to jamestown &amp; yorktown for a week in july and i had an absolutely amazing time.&nbsp; i learned so many things and i now have tons of things to take back to my classroom.&nbsp; i went to new york for a weekend.&nbsp; one of my line sisters is going to michigan for law school and that's what we did with her before she leaves.&nbsp; i had a blast.&nbsp; we did the tourist thing and i got to meet up with a friend of mine from high school overseas who i hadn't seen in 10 years.&nbsp; good times.&nbsp; in between all of that i moved from my apartment to my mom's house.&nbsp; the house is still in a bit of disarray, but it's manageable.&nbsp; 

lately i've noticed that i've become a sympathy crier.&nbsp; for example if one of my friends start&nbsp;crying, my eyes to water.&nbsp; also i've noticed that as i watch tv&nbsp;or&nbsp;movies if there's a sad part my eyes will water as well.&nbsp; it's quite&nbsp;weird.&nbsp; i never&nbsp;used to&nbsp;be effected by stuff like that, and i'm not sure why&nbsp;i am now.&nbsp; &nbsp;i'm not sure i like it. 

this summer my finances are tighter than they have been in four years.&nbsp; it's all because of the idiots in payroll.&nbsp; our summer paychecks are 20% less this summer.&nbsp; it's killing me, especially this past paycheck because i had to pay utilities at both the apartment and the house.&nbsp; on top of that i had other bills. i've dipped into my savings several times and it's dwindling faster than i'd like.&nbsp; something's gotta give&nbsp;or i won't have a&nbsp;savings to dip into.&nbsp; money isn't usually an issue for me, but these paychecks being 20% less&nbsp;has really been hard on my finances.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
i've been a little down this week.&nbsp; in the past week one of my friends&nbsp;moved into a house, another got engaged, and&nbsp;another got married.&nbsp;&nbsp;it seems that all of my friends are doing new and big things in their lives.&nbsp; i feel kind of stuck.&nbsp; kinda like my friends&nbsp;are passing me by.&nbsp; maybe something new or big will happen for me soon.&nbsp; just maybe.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

it's summer vacation.&nbsp; my favorite time of year.&nbsp; i can stay up&nbsp;late and&nbsp;wake up when i want to.&nbsp; it's great.&nbsp; i know that summer break is in full swing because i keep losing track of the days.&nbsp;gotta love being a teacher.&nbsp;

father's day was&nbsp;on sunday.&nbsp; i could have cared less.&nbsp; i didn't bother calling my father&nbsp; it would have been insincere for me to&nbsp;wish him a happy father's&nbsp;day, so i didn't waste his time or mine.&nbsp;&nbsp;it was back in february that i posted a&nbsp;blog about me calling him on his birthday.&nbsp; he said he'd do i better.&nbsp; i wanted to believe him.&nbsp;i still had hope after being disappointed non-stop for the past&nbsp;25 years.&nbsp;i didn't&nbsp;wanna give up on him.&nbsp; i haven't heard&nbsp;from him since i called in february.&nbsp; i&nbsp;don't do this often, but i give up.&nbsp; i'm&nbsp;done trying with him.&nbsp; he won't get another call from me.&nbsp; it's a shame, but it's the way it's gonna be.&nbsp;&nbsp;

it's&nbsp;official my mom will be moving to south&nbsp;carolina&nbsp;in a couple of weeks.&nbsp; she's already&nbsp;paid the security&nbsp;deposit on an apartment.&nbsp;&nbsp;i'll enjoy staying in the house and only paying utilities.&nbsp; i'll get to pay off my credit card and start paying extra on my student loan.&nbsp; i will be able to pay off bills and save money while there.&nbsp;&nbsp;the reason she's moving for awhile&nbsp;is&nbsp;very sad, but it will allow me to really get where i want to be&nbsp;financially.&nbsp;i dread having to pack&nbsp;and move. i have to&nbsp;paint my&nbsp;room&nbsp;before i move back.&nbsp; when i was younger i painted it&nbsp;blue, and not a&nbsp;subtle blue&nbsp;either.&nbsp;&nbsp;as a result i need to paint&nbsp;it a&nbsp;neutral color so&nbsp;it will&nbsp;match my bedroom set and so it looks like an adult lives there and not a middle schooler. &nbsp; &nbsp;

i went to a cookout at a co-worker's house today. everybody there was married and has kids.&nbsp; the person's house we were at was really nice with a nice backyard.&nbsp; it reminded me that i want&nbsp;a husband,&nbsp; a house, and kids.&nbsp; it&nbsp;also reminded me that i don't want kids anytime soon.&nbsp; we were trying to make plans to hang out and they all had to figure out what they were going to do with their child(ren).&nbsp; having kids is a big responsibility and i'm not quite ready for it.&nbsp; i definitely want them, just not&nbsp;soon.&nbsp; i'd like the husband and the house in the near future, but i can wait on the kids.&nbsp; 

i want to go to washington d.c. for a couple of days this summer.&nbsp; i haven't been up there and toured the museums and stuff since i was a kid.&nbsp; i think it'll be fun.&nbsp; now i just have to find someone to go with me, i'm not too fond of the idea of walking around d.c. by myself.&nbsp; 


i anticipate that i will be blogging more often now that it's summer break, and i'll have more free time on my hands.&nbsp; we'll see....&nbsp;&nbsp;

my friend kelsey is my new favorite person.&nbsp; she's funny and&nbsp;a blast&nbsp;to hang out with.&nbsp; not only that but she understands things none of my other friends seem to understand about me.&nbsp; she and i were having a conversation about marriage and discovered&nbsp;we both&nbsp;have the desire to be&nbsp;the &quot;stereotypical&quot; wife.&nbsp; we want to cook dinner and keep&nbsp;the house clean for our future husbands.&nbsp; we want to have dinner ready when he gets home and make lunch for the next day and things like that.&nbsp;not because we feel we&nbsp;have to, but because it's&nbsp;want we want to do.&nbsp;none of my other friends can relate.&nbsp; they think i'm crazy and/or old fashioned when i tell them.&nbsp;&nbsp; as we continued our conversation we&nbsp;started talking about how so many women want and expect all of these grand gestures from men.&nbsp; we agreed that we're more of the quality time kind of girls.&nbsp; she and i both agreed&nbsp;one of the main&nbsp;ways a man can show us he cares is by just spending quality time with us.&nbsp; it's comforting having a friend who understands those things about me and wants the same things.&nbsp; the little things are&nbsp;big to me.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i gave up coffee for lent.&nbsp; it is proving to be quite hard.&nbsp; i guess that's the point,&nbsp;it's&nbsp;supposed to be a sacrifice.&nbsp;&nbsp;

in&nbsp;the month of february three of my&nbsp;friends have gotten engaged.&nbsp; it's an epidemic.&nbsp; it's not surprising since we are at that age.&nbsp; and along those same lines, i have three weddings i have to go to this year.&nbsp; i'm happy for all of them.&nbsp; one day it'll be me.&nbsp; until then, i'll&nbsp;be content&nbsp;being single. =)

so my friends have a habit of not telling me about the things going on in their lives.&nbsp; normally that wouldn't bother me, but they're not telling me things that i think are kind of a big deal. in the past few months i've had friends get engaged, get pregnant, and lose their virginity and none of them told me until months afterward.&nbsp; and these are people i'd consider to be friends,&nbsp; not just associates or acquaintances, a couple of them close friends.&nbsp; what's going on

one of my&nbsp;co-workers&nbsp;is selling her condo so she sent us an email with the link to&nbsp;a virtual tour of her house and it's&nbsp;very nice.&nbsp; it&nbsp;makes me want a&nbsp;house even more.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i really enjoy reading. i wish i had more time&nbsp;to do it during the school year.&nbsp; i always feel like i should be doing something more productive,&nbsp;like grading papers, writing lesson plans, or doing&nbsp;work for&nbsp;grad&nbsp;school.&nbsp;&nbsp;

my&nbsp;assistant principal&nbsp;had really been riding me lately.&nbsp;&nbsp;the social studies benchmark scores weren't as high as she would have liked them, so she's giving me shit about it.&nbsp;&nbsp;i'll admit, there were some low scores, but i do teach social studies to the entire fourth grade.&nbsp; it's kinda&nbsp;hard making sure 96 students get 80% or better.&nbsp;&nbsp;i love history and i love teaching&nbsp;social studies,&nbsp;but i do&nbsp;feel a&nbsp;lot of pressure.&nbsp;&nbsp;bleck.

overall life is pretty good.&nbsp; i'm happy as well as content.&nbsp; it's a good feeling.&nbsp; i hope it lasts.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

maybe i'm moody, or emotional, or even crazy, but sometimes i feel complete and absolute disdain toward a person.&nbsp;&nbsp; then later i feel as if my heart is going to burst because i just care for them so much.&nbsp; and the crazy thing is, nothing will have changed&nbsp;from the&nbsp;time i felt the first emotion to the time i felt the second.&nbsp; is that weird?

sometimes i teeter between action and inaction.&nbsp; not because i'm afraid, but because i'm not sure my actions, whatever they may be at the time, will make any difference.&nbsp; with some people it doesn't matter what you say or do. so do you bother saying it or doing it?&nbsp; do you not even bother because it won't matter or&nbsp;do you say or do it because maybe this time it will?&nbsp; my teetering is often increased because of the responses&nbsp;i receive.&nbsp; sometimes they're positive, sometimes they're negative, and sometimes i don't get a response at all.&nbsp; it's always a gamble.&nbsp; my action or inaction really depends on if i feel lucky.&nbsp; more&nbsp;often than not, i don't.&nbsp;&nbsp;

they often&nbsp;say that a girl's relationship with guys emulates the&nbsp;relationship she has with her father.&nbsp; hmm.&nbsp; what does that say about me?

i love spending time with my family.&nbsp;&nbsp;i enjoy their company and they make me laugh.&nbsp; i wished we&nbsp;lived closer to them.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i'd love to get some answers soon. 

sometimes i listen to a song and i feel it all the way in&nbsp;the bottom of my heart and with every fiber of my being.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

a few random thoughts: 

1.&nbsp; i've recently fallen in love with starbucks. now i see why people are so addicted to it.&nbsp; lately i've definitely become much more of a coffee drinker, so i decided to put the starbucks gift cards i had to use.&nbsp; i've loved each drink that i've gotten.&nbsp; i don't plan on making going to starbucks a habit because it's just too expensive, but as long as i have gift cards i will be partaking in their delightful drinks. 

2.&nbsp; i really enjoy watching the food network.&nbsp; i have watched iron chef a couple of times and i really like it.&nbsp; i enjoy watching people put together all different kinds of food.&nbsp; 

3.&nbsp; i really want to buy a house. but unfortunately i&nbsp;can't afford it on my own&nbsp;right now.&nbsp; that's why i need a husband. haha.&nbsp; on that note, i see&nbsp;why some people get married for financial stability rather than love.&nbsp;&nbsp;call me&nbsp;crazy or old fashioned, but i actually wanna get married for love, not money.&nbsp; although both would be quite nice.&nbsp; 

4.&nbsp; what precisely constitutes a genuine friendship?&nbsp; does it matter if one person is doing most of the contacting?&nbsp;can the friendship truly&nbsp;grow if the friends don't&nbsp;really&nbsp;have meaningful conversation&nbsp;or spend any time together?&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; friendship about getting to know a person and growing closer?&nbsp;&nbsp;can anything be done&nbsp;to change things?&nbsp;&nbsp; 

5.&nbsp;&nbsp;i'm waiting on a miracle.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

&nbsp;life is a roller coaster.&nbsp; you have ups, you have downs, there are loops, at times you feel like you're turning upside down, sometimes life goes by so fast, others it's like you're going uphill oh so slowly.&nbsp; it's no wonder people, including me, are so emotional.&nbsp; how can you not be dealing with all of the things life throws at you.&nbsp; i know for a fact that it's that way for me.&nbsp; there really was no point in saying all that, just an observation.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i have thoroughly been enjoying my summer vacation.&nbsp; last week i was pretty much a bum the entire time.&nbsp; this week i'm taking a grad class.&nbsp; i'm quite pleased with it.&nbsp; it is actually something that will be useful.&nbsp; i've already learned a few things that i plan on using next year.&nbsp; in addition there isn't that much work involved.&nbsp; we have three presentations this week, and then the rest of the work is due in august.&nbsp; that includes reading two articles and doing a one-page write up, and then creating ten activities that involve technology.&nbsp; not hard.&nbsp; i plan on creating things that i can use next year.&nbsp; if i haven't mentioned before i'll be teaching just social studies next year.&nbsp; i am excited about it!&nbsp; social studies is my favorite subject to teach. i'll only have to plan for one subject.&nbsp; on top of that i won't have to do all of the crap that goes along with reading. woohoo! granted i will have to teach the same thing 4 times, but there are drawbacks to everything.&nbsp; oh well.&nbsp; on saturday i'm leaving for vegas.&nbsp; i'm excited.&nbsp; i've never been and it should be fun.&nbsp; after that i don't have anything planned for the rest of the summer.&nbsp; there are a couple of things i'd like to do around the apartment, but nothing serious.&nbsp;&nbsp;

today was a good day.&nbsp; i felt a sense of contentment and peace.&nbsp; it was as if nothing could bring me down.&nbsp; it was definitely a good feeling.&nbsp; i hope it continues.&nbsp;&nbsp;

it's amazing the types of things people can teach you without even trying.&nbsp; i've learned things about life and myself from just the interaction with certain people.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i think when i decided to write this blog i had more substantial things to write.&nbsp;i don't know what happened.

now i see why there aren't black people in the NHL.&nbsp; that's because ice skating isn't easy.&nbsp; i'm a decent skater so i thought perhaps ice skating would be similar.&nbsp; while it is, there's the whole this is ice and it's slippery, hard and cold and i don't wanna fall on it factor.&nbsp; and it didn't help that not even five minutes after we got there a man fell and had to be taken away on a gurney.&nbsp; that wasn't encouraging....at all.&nbsp;&nbsp; for awhile i was skating and holding on to the rail, i wasn't tryna lose my life.&nbsp; but after awhile i got the hang of it and was able to skate without holding onto the rail. i skated right next to it thought, just in case. overall i had fun. (even though my back really hurts as a result) 

today my assistant principal came to observe me.&nbsp; normally i'm not too nervous or worried about being observed, but this time i was.&nbsp; it's because my assistant principal is a know nit-picker.&nbsp; i could do 98 out of 100 things right and she spend 10 seconds on what i did right and 10 minutes on the things i've done wrong.&nbsp; then on top of that she doesn't tell me how to improve it. blah.&nbsp; anyway, because i knew she was coming i was able to dread it.&nbsp; my teaching partner and i were talking about how knowing our observations were coming up (mine today, his tomorrow) that it put a damper on our weekend.&nbsp; we both agreed that it was hard to forget about it and enjoy the weekend.&nbsp; and even more so since it since she's been extra nit-picky in the past few months.&nbsp; it was apparently bothering me more than i thought because i didn't sleep very well last night, and this morning i was having a hard time focusing.&nbsp; every so often my mind would drift back to my observation, worrying if i'd have enough time to clean my room? what is she gonna say about my gradebook? my lesson plans? etc.&nbsp; it was weird, i was nervous all the way up until the moment she walked into my classroom (late, i might add....she's such a hypocrite).&nbsp; after that it was like, i'm doing what i love to do, i don't care what you think.&nbsp; my lesson went really well, my kids were well behaved, and i feel pretty confident about it all.&nbsp; we shall see after i have my post observation conference.&nbsp;&nbsp;

there was one more thing i wanted to talk about, but i'm tired from not getting much sleep last night and my back is really killing me.&nbsp; so i'ma take some motrin and go to bed.&nbsp; maybe i'll get around to posting again tomorrow.&nbsp;&nbsp;

i've thoroughly been enjoying my break.&nbsp; it feels so good to not have to set my alarm clock.&nbsp; waking up whenever i feel like it has been fabulous.&nbsp; because my body is so used to waking up at 6:30 i can't seem to sleep past about 9 or so, but even those extra hours have been wonderful.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

it's rare that i call people because i have something going on and i need to talk.&nbsp; but it seems that when i do, nobody i call is ever able to talk.&nbsp; perhaps that's why i don't bother most times.&nbsp; i know it's not their fault, but it can still be discouraging.&nbsp; ah, oh well, that's life i suppose.

lately i've been watching football.&nbsp; in a previous post i said i wanted to learn more about football and actually enjoy watching the game, and that i have.&nbsp; more so the enjoy watching the game than the learning more about it.&nbsp; i don't know much more than i did before, but i'm able to enjoy it with what knowledge i do have.&nbsp; i noticed if you listen to the guys talking they'll explain some things, but i still have some questions.&nbsp;like what is a blitz? if you ask me, it&nbsp;sounds like something i can order at IHOP.&nbsp; and what exactly does a half back, full back, safety, tight end (although if you ask me they all have nice&nbsp;tight ends in those tight little football pants ;) , etc. do?&nbsp;and if there's a wide receiver why is there no narrow receiver?&nbsp;i tried&nbsp;looking it up on the internet (like i do&nbsp;almost everything when i don't understand something) and it got me nowhere.&nbsp; i didn't really understand what the heck they were&nbsp;saying.&nbsp;my efforts to watch football with someone who understands and can explain haven't been too successful lately, so&nbsp;i tried watching with my mom,&nbsp;who likes and claims she understands football.&nbsp; that may be true, but she is a HORRIBLE explainer, oh my gosh.&nbsp; 

with the ending of one year and the starting of a new one it makes me reflect on the past year.&nbsp; i've looked back on the positives and negatives to see what went well and what didn't.&nbsp; i look at the ways in which i've changed and grown.&nbsp; i take a look at what things i can keep the same and what things i need to change.&nbsp; and at the end of this year i need to re-evaluate my friendships.&nbsp; i find that i've&nbsp;put a lot of&nbsp;time and effort into some friendships only for them to be one-sided.&nbsp; i hate to feel like i'm giving up on people, but sometimes it just has to be that way, especially with those friendships in which i feel that i'm the only one contributing to the survival of the friendship.&nbsp; a relationship of any kind requires both people to put in work, and it's just not fair to me if i'm the only who's really putting forth the effort, and that's how it feels.&nbsp; i'm not ending the friendships completely, although that's probably what i should do.&nbsp; i'm just not putting as much time and effort into friendships&nbsp;i feel are one-sided.&nbsp; it sounds like a no brainer and like it'll be something that's easy.&nbsp; i tend to put my all into my friendships and&nbsp;i take it pretty personally when they seem to be faling, even if it's not my fault.&nbsp; so to not put my all into something, more specifically someone is going to be&nbsp;difficult for me.&nbsp;&nbsp;people make time for the things and people who are important to them, so if i'm not important enough for them to make time, or put forth effort then i'm not gonna go outta my way for them.&nbsp; on the other hand there have been positive things that have come out of this year. one&nbsp;of those&nbsp;is my ability to recover.&nbsp; i'm an emotional and sensitive person, i can't help it, that's&nbsp;just the way i am.&nbsp; but this year, i have learned to recover and bounce back from&nbsp;things more quickly.&nbsp; the ability to do that&nbsp;has definitely&nbsp;had a positive impact in my life.&nbsp; i'm not&nbsp;big on resolutions,&nbsp;they just end&nbsp;up being broken anyway.&nbsp; last year i only made one resolution and that was to pray more, and i accomplished that.&nbsp;&nbsp;so this year, i'm making a similar resolution so to speak.&nbsp; in the last half of&nbsp;2007 my relationship with God has grown stonger, and my "resolution" for 2008 is to seek God in all that I do and to continue to grow in Christ.&nbsp; And it just occured to me that&nbsp;because of this 'resolution' i'm going to place my failing friendships in his&nbsp;hands, and i pray that he'll do what he sees fit with them.&nbsp;&nbsp;i'd really love to seem them improved, i really would.&nbsp; i really feel that God has&nbsp;been working in me and that he has good things waiting for me in&nbsp;2008 and i can't wait&nbsp;until he shows me what they are.&nbsp; so,&nbsp;as&nbsp;2007&nbsp;ends and 2008 begins, i&nbsp;pray that you and yours are blessed.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

&nbsp;tomorrow is the last day of work before christmas break.&nbsp; i can't wait!&nbsp; my kids have been nutty for the past two weeks.&nbsp; it gets worse with each passing day.&nbsp; i know they'll be completely loony and outta their minds tomorrow.&nbsp; thank God it's early release!&nbsp; after that i'll be student-free for a week and a half. it'll be glorious.&nbsp; 

i hate the cold weather.&nbsp; one reason being i just hate being cold.&nbsp; another is, i find that my back hurts more often and more painfully in the winter. blah.&nbsp; on top of that my nails tend to break more in the winter.&nbsp;&nbsp;it's also so much harder to get outta bed in the&nbsp;winter time.&nbsp; one thing i do like about winter is&nbsp;curling up&nbsp;on the couch with a blanket&nbsp;and reading or watching&nbsp;t.v.&nbsp;&nbsp;i'll have to make sure i do that over the break. 

on friday my roommate is going home for&nbsp;like a week.&nbsp; i enjoy having a roommate, but it's also nice&nbsp;having the apartment to myself.&nbsp;&nbsp;every time she goes home i always joke that i'm gonna have a wild party and have lots of strippers.&nbsp; we both get a kick outta that because she and i both know that is definitely not something i'd do.&nbsp; i'll probably end up just hanging&nbsp;around looking for something to do.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

lately i've been doing a lot&nbsp;of thinking.&nbsp; in doing all of this thinking&nbsp;i've come to&nbsp;some conclusions.&nbsp; that in itself is a whole separate blog that i'll probably write at a later date, not making any promises though.&nbsp;



&nbsp;

not too much as been going on.&nbsp; just a bunch of randomness really.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

last sunday i was flossing my teeth and saw that it looked like one of my fillings was coming out. so i made a dentist appointment on monday and surely enough it was coming out.&nbsp; actually my dentist said i broke the filling.&nbsp; how you break a metal filling, i haven't the slightest idea, but apparently i did.&nbsp; so anyway he replaced it (with a white filling, so now you can't even see where it is) and i'm good to go.&nbsp; although from the middle of my mouth up to my right ear was number for like 4 hours. good times.&nbsp; now i'm extra paranoid because the filling was in one of the two baby teeth i have (no adult teeth ever grew in) so i wanna make sure that it doesn't fall out anytime soon, and i had&nbsp;been chewing on only the left side of my mouth.&nbsp; let me tell you, that gets tiring.&nbsp; i've finally started chewing on the right side again, but i'm extra cautious. 

&nbsp;as you may or may not know , the week before last my principal came to do my yearly observation (i only have to get observed once a year from here on out. yay!)&nbsp; i thought it went pretty well.&nbsp; i wasn't nervous or anything before she came.&nbsp; i'm not sure if that's because i was that confident or because i dislike my principal so&nbsp;much, i wasn't really concerned. haha. either way, she came observed me, and left a bit early because there was an emergency in the school that she had to take care of.&nbsp; i thought it went pretty well.&nbsp; but the point of the story is this.&nbsp; on friday at the end of the day she says that she needs to see 7 teachers, me included (even though half the names she called weren't the right people...that just shows you how much of an idiot she is.) so i pack my things and go to the office to find out that she wants to have our post-observation conference....on a friday afternoon!!!!&nbsp; i was quite perturbed.&nbsp; there were 4 people ahead of me and each conference seemed to take forever.&nbsp; so needless to say i didn't leave work on friday afternoon until like 5:45.&nbsp; i was soo mad!&nbsp; it's not my fault that the post-observation conferences were due downtown that day.&nbsp; once again, my principal is an idiot.&nbsp; but at any rate she had nothing but positive things to say.&nbsp; She didn't have anything negative to say about my lesson plans, which is a first because administration ALWAYS has something to say about my lesson plans.&nbsp; then again i did start putting effort into writing better plans this year....hmm, perhaps that made the difference. haha.&nbsp; i felt pretty good afterward...except the fact that i left work at 5:45 on a friday evening!&nbsp; grrr&nbsp; i am really excited that this tuesday is a teacher workday so we won't have any kids, and next monday is veteran's day so i don't even have to go to work.&nbsp; then the week after that is thanksgiving break.&nbsp; woohoo, for november being a month with lots of day off!&nbsp; then all i have to do is make it through i few weeks in december and we're off for christmas break.&nbsp; when i look at it that way it's totally manageable.&nbsp; the only then between now and then that'll slow me down is report cards.&nbsp; i HATE doing report card crap.&nbsp; blah.&nbsp; but whatever, it'll be ok, especially since each year gets a bit easier.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

bills suck.&nbsp; 

i figured out why i had been having a hard time sleeping the past few weeks.&nbsp; it was because i was having trouble breathing so i wasn't sleeping well, and on top of that i had this cough that wouldn't go away.&nbsp; i noticed it one night when i was falling asleep and had to wake up because i wasn't getting enough air.&nbsp; so for a good two weeks i wasn't getting good sleep because at about 8 or 9 my chest would start to get really tight and i couldn't breathe very well.&nbsp; this past week hasn't been too bad and i've been able to fall asleep (most nights) and i've definitely been able to tell the difference.&nbsp; so let's hope it stays that way.&nbsp; otherwise i'm gonna have to make a doctor's appointment to see what's going on.&nbsp; man, i have never been so sickly and&nbsp;such as i have in these past few months.&nbsp; i usually have a pretty good immune system.&nbsp; what on earth is going on?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 

i can be a bit of a perfecitonist at times.&nbsp; it's not all the time and it's not with everything.&nbsp; the other day i&nbsp;was writing something, and i know that i read it and revised it about 20 times before&nbsp;i was satisfied.&nbsp; i was going to write it by hand but then i knew that i'd want to change it numerous times so it was just more practical to type it.&nbsp; i find that it's usually when i'm writing something or making something for somebody&nbsp;that everything has to be just so before i'm satisfied with it.&nbsp; i'm not sure why that is, but whatever.&nbsp; i'm fine with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 

other than a couple of personal things, not much else is going on....not like that comes as a big surprise.&nbsp;&nbsp; i shall return later with more randomness.&nbsp; until then, leave comments!

so i've been doing a lot of thinking today.&nbsp; not necessarily on purpose, it just kinda happened.&nbsp; there are two things that i've been thinking about.&nbsp; one of them popped into my head while driving to work, and the other came from the guest speaker we had at convocation today. i'm gonna attempt to put in writing what was going on in my head...i'm not sure how well that's gonna work, but here goes....i hope it makes sense....

just to give you a little background, let me tell you what the speaker was talking about.&nbsp; he was saying how he and his wife had a daughter and she passed away of cancer at age 3.&nbsp; the students at his school started a tree of life in which they donated money.&nbsp; he said it wasn't the fact that they were giving money that touched him but that they were trying to do something in the first place.&nbsp; well he was saying he went back to work on the last day and there had been this boy who had given him trouble all year.&nbsp; this boy caused trouble when he expected and he presented him with surprises and caused trouble when he least expected it.&nbsp; well anyway he was saying that on the last day of school, this boy who had caused various amounts of trouble all year was walking out of the door (leaving middle school for high school) and turned around and told the speaker that he didn't have much but he wanted to give the only dime he had to the tree of life to support his daughter.&nbsp; the speaker was saying how much that touched him because the boy could have just walked away and that would have been it.&nbsp; but he was touched because when the trouble maker boy did that he should him who he was, and at that point it didn't matter how he had behaved.&nbsp; the speaker was saying that we as teachers have to care about students for who they are and not how they behave.&nbsp; when i thought about it i realized how true that is.&nbsp; but then i realized that that could be applied to more than just students.&nbsp; in life we care about people for who they are and not how they behave....well most of the time.&nbsp; i&nbsp;mean think about, if your friend has a bad day, or someone you care about is a complete asshole&nbsp;to you, you don't just say f***k them because they're behaving badly.&nbsp; you care about them for who they are, cuss them out, ignore them for awhile or whatever, but that doesn't necessarily change how you feel about them.&nbsp; well it shouldn't, not if you truly care about them for who they are.&nbsp; this becomes apparent when people are looking in on a situation that one of their friends are in.&nbsp; take for instance, one of my friends had someone close to them treat them pretty crappy.&nbsp; he was not a very good friend to her, and some of us were telling her to ditch him and stop being friends with him&nbsp;or whatever because he wasn't behaving in a manner in which we felt he should.&nbsp;&nbsp;she saw that he was behaving like the biggest&nbsp;ass on the face of the planet, but she still stayed friends with him because of who he was, not how he happened to be&nbsp;behaving.&nbsp;&nbsp;so i stopped to think about it, and realized that that's the case in my life.&nbsp; a couple of people i know can really suck at life sometimes and be complete jerks, BUT i care deeply about them and&nbsp;i focus more on who they are, and less on how they behave.&nbsp; now as i type this i know some of you are thinking that that means these people are getting&nbsp;away with&nbsp;behaving badly and we're just letting them get away with&nbsp;it.&nbsp; that's not that case, you can still be upset about how they're behaving, or disagree completely with the way they're acting, but&nbsp;genuinely caring about someone means loving them in spite of their imperfections. i think about it like this.&nbsp; God can't stand the way we behave when we sin and do things against him, BUT he still loves and cares about us.&nbsp; sometimes he punishes us, and let's us know he's not happy with the way we behave, but he doesn't EVER love or care about us any less.&nbsp; it's practically the same thing with the people in our lives. 

the other thing is actually kinda like two things in one.&nbsp; the other week at church and at my small group the topic of being transparent with people came up.&nbsp; and so i started thinking about the concept and all it entails.&nbsp; i came to the conclusion that there are 2 sometimes 3 people that i'm pretty transparent with.&nbsp; i'm me with no apologies, they see the good, the bad, the happy, the sad, the emotional, the irrational, the insane, the who or whatever it is at the moment.&nbsp; i'm 100% me all of the time.&nbsp; and it's not that i'm not me around everyone i know, it's just that everyone doesn't get to see the depths of all that i am....if that makes sense.&nbsp; but anyway, it obviously wasn't always like that.&nbsp; so i got to thinking about how something like that happens.&nbsp; because being transparent with someone means presenting your vulnerability and most people don't like that.&nbsp; i came to the conclusion that for someone to be transparent with another person they have to really trust that person.&nbsp; and that usually only comes when both people are being transparent with each other.&nbsp; trusting people is a sticky situation in itself because it can lead to people getting hurt.&nbsp; now i know that if these people ever betray me&nbsp;i will be absolutely devastated, i'm not even gonna lie.&nbsp; but on the other hand, i can't live my whole entire life not trusting anybody....that'd lead to a lonely life, plus it just seems like too much work to keep all that in, but hey, that's just me.&nbsp; and the other thing that goes along with this is people and the walls they've built.&nbsp; everyone, nobody how trusting or not,&nbsp;has some type of wall that they've built in order to protect themselves. and in my opinion everyone wants someone to break down this wall....or at least try. but things get complicated when you think about the types of walls people have built and how people approach these walls.&nbsp;&nbsp;let me see if i can't explain what i mean.&nbsp;&nbsp;it's kinda like the three little&nbsp;pigs.&nbsp; some people build their walls out of straw, some&nbsp;out of sticks, and some of out of bricks.&nbsp; in&nbsp;a lot of cases&nbsp;when people try to break down the walls people have built they kind of charge at the wall and hopes it falls. if the person has built their wall outta straw or sticks, that method&nbsp;works.&nbsp; but in most cases people build walls to protect themselves from something so they build it out of something sturdy, like bricks.&nbsp; so in that case the running and charging at the brick wall doesn't work.&nbsp; and depending on the person, after running and charging at&nbsp;the wall a few&nbsp;time and&nbsp;nothing happening is reason enough to give up and not put anymore effort into breaking the walls down.&nbsp;&nbsp;when that happens that shows the person behind the wall that the person trying to break down the wall doesn't care too much about what's&nbsp;really&nbsp;behind the wall....thus giving them more reason to keep the wall up.&nbsp;&nbsp;but sometimes you get people who are a bit more patient and are willing to put in the time and effort to&nbsp;try and break down the wall by slowly chipping away small pieces.&nbsp; they realize that a wall isn't gonna come down overnight and with one or two attempts.&nbsp; but the problem with that is, most people&nbsp;usually aren't willing to&nbsp;put in the time and effort to chip away at the wall, they&nbsp;want&nbsp;immediate results.&nbsp;&nbsp;immediate results are much more gratifying&nbsp;for a couple of reasons.&nbsp; one being the person breaking down the wall feels they have accomplished something.&nbsp;and the other is chipping away at the wall is like taking a chance.&nbsp; if they put in the energy to do so and don't like what they find on the other side or it's not what they thought it was they feel as if they've wasted their time and energy....something they can't ever get back...hence why people give up after a few tries.&nbsp; but on the other hand if what's on the other side is important enough to you, you'll keep chipping away at the bricks.&nbsp; and sometimes you chip away the bricks, get a real glimpse of what's behind the wall and then the person puts new bricks in the place of the ones that were removed, and you feel as if you're starting all over.&nbsp; in my opinion if you keep chipping away at the bricks it shows the person behind the wall one of two things.&nbsp; it shows them that either you're a crazy stalker, or that you're someone who really cares enough about what's behind the wall to continue to put your time, energy and effort into breaking it down.&nbsp;now the person behind the wall may or may not ever let you really see what's back there, but&nbsp;that's just the risk you take.&nbsp; as for me, i think i'm gonna keep chipping away for a little while longer....&nbsp;

